The number of observations \( \leq 27.3 \) follows a binomial distribution with parameters \( n = 8 \) and \( p = 0.7 \). Thus,  
\[ P(S \geq 7) = P(S = 7) + P(S = 8), \]  
where \( S \) is the binomial random variable.

Calculations yield:  
\[ P(S = 7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3 \approx 0.19765032, \]  
