Solution: The probability of visiting at least one of the therapists is \(100\% - 8\% = 92\%\), since \(8\%\) visit neither. Let \(P(C)\) be the probability of visiting a chiropractor and \(P(P)\) be the probability of visiting a physical therapist. Given that \(P(P)\) exceeds \(P(C)\) by \(16\%\) (absolute percentage points), so \(P(P) = P(C) + 16\%\).

