100% - (16% + 19%) = 65%.  

Next, the joint percentages are found:  
- The percentage with irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure is 35% of 17% = 0.35 × 17 = 5.95%.  
- The percentage with irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure is 11% of 65% = 0.11 × 65 = 7.15%.  

