For low blood pressure patients, the percentage with a regular heartbeat is derived as:  
Percentage with low blood pressure minus percentage with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure:  
19% - 3.90% = 15.10%.  

Rounding 15.10% to a reasonable number of significant figures (based on input data with 2-3 significant figures) gives 15.1%.  

