Solution: The probability that there is at least one match when each of the 12 students rolls their 12-sided die is calculated as the complement of the probability of no matches. Since each die roll is independent and fair, the probability that a specific student does not roll their own number is \( \frac{11}{12} \). Therefore, the probability that no student rolls their own number is \( \left( \frac{11}{12} \right)^{12} \).

